scheinung und Reflexion von Schönheit. Bildung wird dabei als rezeptive Erfahrung und Interpretation von Schönheit sowie als produktive Formung und Gestaltung des Schönen - nicht zuletzt des schönen Lebens - verstanden.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aSocial SciencesxEducationxEducation, other. 4aBildung. 4aBildungstheorie. 4aGeschmack. 4aKunst. 4aPädagogik. 7aEDUCATION / Philosophy, Theory & Social Aspects.2bisacsh  aArts.  aEducation.  aPedagogy.  aTheory of Education.1 aAckermann, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBubmann, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDickel, Hans, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEngelhardt, Michael von, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKiek, Konrad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKugelmann, Claudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLangenhorst, Georg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLiebau, Eckart, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLiebau, Eckart, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRoch, Eckhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRuisinger, Marion Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchoenmakers, Henri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSeel, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStudt, André, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZirfas, Jörg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZirfas, Jörg, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt0